de99ison2017-06-01 20:13:512017-06-01 22:11:45Aurora Plastics Announces Acquisition of Reinier Plastics Aurora Plastics Announces the Appointment of Charlotte Fischer as Western Sales Manager			 February 13, 2017/in Uncategorized /by de99ison



STREETSBORO, Ohio – (February 13, 2017) – Aurora Plastics, a leading manufacturer of high quality PVC compounds in both powder and pellet form for a variety of plastic applications, announces the appointment of Charlotte Fischer as Western Sales Manager.
Charlotte will assume responsibility for this region servicing our current customers and working to aggressively grow the territory and customer base. The Western Region territory includes the following States and Provinces: Alaska, Alberta, Arizona, British Columbia, California, Colorado, Idaho, Iowa, Montana, Nevada, New Mexico, Oregon, Saskatchewan, Utah, Washington and Wyoming.
Prior to joining Aurora, Charlotte worked in the plastics recycling industry as a Sales Consultant. Other positions held include, Director of Sales/Marketing for Berg Mill Supply, Sr. Sales Manager for Georgia Pacific Harmon Recycling and Primeline Polymers as a Plastic Resin Sales Representative. She graduated from California State Polytechnic University with a Bachelor of Science in Journalism/Communication. Charlotte resides in Lakeside, CA.
Charlotte brings an abundance of sales experience; including key account management and consultative / technical sales, which will be important in meeting our sales plan and company goals and objectives. “I’m exciting to welcome Charlotte to the Aurora Plastics’ Sales Team. Her years of experience servicing the plastics’ industry will be a great foundation to help Charlotte assist our customers in the West” said Steve Harrigan, VP of Sales.
Charlotte can be reached by phone at (619) 873-7008.


