de99ison2016-11-22 14:59:192016-11-22 15:12:50Aurora Plastics Announces ISO 9001:2008 with Design Recertification – This recognition highlights company’s continued commitment to quality. Aurora Plastics Announces the Appointment of Robert Littell as Senior Director, New Business Development			 November 21, 2016/in Uncategorized /by de99ison



STREETSBORO, Ohio – (November 21, 2016) – Aurora Plastics, a leading manufacturer of high quality PVC compounds in both powder and pellet form for a variety of plastic applications, announces the appointment of Robert “Bob” Littell to its commercial organization as senior. director of new business development.
In this newly formed position on the sales team, LIttell will assume responsibility for identifying and executing new customer relationships, geographical expansions and penetration into new market segments. He will drive new product offerings and establish strategic partnerships.
Prior to joining Aurora Plastics, Littell spent his career at PolyOne/Geon/BF Goodrich in various roles, including commercial director, general manager and in sales. In his sales leadership roles, he served on the leadership team focusing on custom extruders, pipe and fittings, electrical, and the wire and cable market.
“Bob brings an abundance of experience and a proven track record of success in business development, sales, and strategic planning, which will be invaluable in meeting our growth objectives,” says Steve Harrigan, vice presdent of sales at Aurora Plastics.
Littell holds a master’s degree in business administration from Cleveland State University and a bachelor’s degree in business administration from Penn State University.
Headquartered in Streetsboro, Ohio, Aurora Plastics was founded in 1997, and employs commercial and technical experts who have more than 500 years of polymer industry experience. The company is 100% focused on PVC and related blends, and has the two newest ISO 9001:2008 facilities in the industry – offering more than 500 million pounds of blending capacity. The company’s unparalleled lead time to shipment, strict quality policies, customer service and in-field technical support differentiate them from other compounders in the industry.
For more information on Aurora Plastics or the recent appointments, please contact Matthew Kuwatch, Vice President, Marketing & Business Development, +1 330 626 6423, mkuwatch@auroraplastics.com.


