de99ison2015-10-21 13:07:452016-11-10 15:33:29Aurora Plastics Brands Its Cellular PVC Foam and PVC Capstock Product Lines Under the New AuroraLite™ and AuroraShield™ Names Aurora Plastics Sets New Standard for Low-Density Cellular Foams			 March 20, 2015/in Uncategorized /by Kevin RastAURORA PLASTICS SETS NEW STANDARD FOR LOW-DENSITY CELLULAR FOAMS
New Product Offering Features Lowest Densities in the Industry
STREETSBORO, OH (March 20, 2015) — Aurora Plastics Inc., a leading manufacturer of rigid and foam PVC, has raised the bar in the industry with a new low-density cellular PVC foam.  Aurora Plastics offers a product line available in the .35 – .80 density range, which includes some of the lowest density cellular foams in the industry.  The end result is a highly lightweight, yet durable, material that is ideal for an array of interior decorative applications.  It will be showcased at NPE2015 in Orlando in March 2015 (BOOTH #S15061).
“Aurora Plastics continues to focus on discovering unmet needs and creating solutions for our customers,” said Matthew Kuwatch, vice president of marketing and business development for Aurora Plastics.  “Combined with our unwavering commitment to excellence in both product quality and service our team strives to provide our customers value in every product they purchase from Aurora Plastics.”
With two of the newest ISO 9001:2008 certified production facilities in the industry and an ongoing commitment to investing in new material technology platforms, Aurora Plastics continues to lead the industry in innovation, quality and technical support.  Its unparalleled seven-day lead time to shipment additionally means that customers can save costs by maintaining lower inventory levels yet still meet tight production orders.
To learn more, visit Aurora Plastics at its booth at NPE2015 (#S15061), call 330-422-0700 or visit www.auroraplastics.com.
About the Company
Aurora Plastics Inc. is a leader in the manufacture of high-quality exterior weatherable RPVC (Rigid PVC), interior grade RPVC, cellular foam RPVC, injection molding compounds, PVC/acrylic alloy cap stock, as well as custom and tolled compounds in both powder and pellet form.  Headquartered in Streetsboro, Ohio, the company has the two newest ISO 9001:2008 certified PVC production facilities in the U.S. with a total blending capacity of more than 500 million pounds.  Unlike other manufacturers in the market, Aurora Plastics is 100% focused on PVC and related blends.  Its extensive technical support team, which consists of highly seasoned industry professionals, is available to provide onsite support during trials and throughout the production process.


